The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, May 23, 2004 				 New Horizon to expand
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, May 22: New Horizon India, a 20:80 joint venture between US-based infotech training major New Horizon and Shriram Group Technologies, has outlined an investment of Rs 200 crore over the next three years to consolidate its position in the country.																								The company is actively targeting the corporate and government training segments as part of its growth strategy in India.																								The investment will cover activities related to setting up both company-owned and franchisee centres.																								We plan to set up 250 centres over the next three years, said Nirmal Kumar, head (education and training). During the current year, 45 centres will be set up across India. 
